Text.SourceString: It’s good to see you out and about.//Have you introduced yourself to the townies?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to see you out and about.//Have you introduced yourself to the townies?

Text.SourceString: We’ve been setting aside recyclables in that lot near the park.//I’m hoping someday we can build something there.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ve been setting aside recyclables in that lot near the park.//I’m hoping someday we can build something there.

Text.SourceString: I think people here already have the right mindset to reduce, reuse, and recycle.//It’s a shame we don’t have an appropriate facility for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I think people here already have the right mindset to reduce, reuse, and recycle.//It’s a shame we don’t have an appropriate facility for it.

Text.SourceString: Our goal is to build a recycling center for the locals.//Hopefully, we can teach our youth, and they can carry the tradition forward.
Text.LocalizedString: Our goal is to build a recycling center for the locals.//Hopefully, we can teach our youth, and they can carry the tradition forward.

Text.SourceString: Can you imagine how much trash there actually is in the ocean?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you imagine how much trash there actually is in the ocean?

Text.SourceString: I hope we can clean up the trash on the ocean floor someday so we can finally start our coral reef nursery.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope we can clean up the trash on the ocean floor someday so we can finally start our coral reef nursery.

Text.SourceString: Looking for some work to do, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Ah, I was just thinking, Wouldn’t it be nice if we could have a community garden?
Text.LocalizedString: Looking for some work to do, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Ah, I was just thinking, Wouldn’t it be nice if we could have a community garden?

Text.SourceString: It would be nice to have a place where the community could grow crops, share produce, and form bonds.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be nice to have a place where the community could grow crops, share produce, and form bonds.

Text.SourceString: There’s a list of community upgrades we can do.//It’s in the community center.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a list of community upgrades we can do.//It’s in the community center.

Text.SourceString: There aren’t that many items on the list right now, but I think we should add to it as we see how our island progresses.
Text.LocalizedString: There aren’t that many items on the list right now, but I think we should add to it as we see how our island progresses.

Text.SourceString: How was your weekend?//<portrait=happy>I’m going to start this week off with a cup of the Tavern’s coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your weekend?//<portrait=happy>I’m going to start this week off with a cup of the Tavern’s coffee.

Text.SourceString: I got some and kept it in the fridge over the weekend.//You know, I save the cups and use them as planters.
Text.LocalizedString: I got some and kept it in the fridge over the weekend.//You know, I save the cups and use them as planters.

Text.SourceString: It must take plenty of work to get your farm ready for planting every season.
Text.LocalizedString: It must take plenty of work to get your farm ready for planting every season.

Text.SourceString: I’m no farmer, but clearing weeds is probably the first step.//Would you agree?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m no farmer, but clearing weeds is probably the first step.//Would you agree?

Text.SourceString: I don’t think you need a fancy tool for it.//I believe your standard scythe will do.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think you need a fancy tool for it.//I believe your standard scythe will do.

Text.SourceString: If you want to upgrade any of your tools, take them to the <NpcName>Sanchezes’</> shop.//They know what they’re doing.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to upgrade any of your tools, take them to the <NpcName>Sanchezes’</> shop.//They know what they’re doing.

Text.SourceString: They live in the woodland, just across the creek from my house.
Text.LocalizedString: They live in the woodland, just across the creek from my house.

Text.SourceString: Did you really see a merperson?//<portrait=happy>Ah! You got me again. Nice one, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you really see a merperson?//<portrait=happy>Ah! You got me again. Nice one, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I admit, shopping can get addictive.
Text.LocalizedString: I admit, shopping can get addictive.

Text.SourceString: I should probably update the bulletin board tomorrow and make sure there aren’t any outdated posts.
Text.LocalizedString: I should probably update the bulletin board tomorrow and make sure there aren’t any outdated posts.

Text.SourceString: If you want to keep track of people’s birthdays, there’s a calendar near <NPCName>Sam</>’s General Store.//Don’t worry, I make sure to update it every season.//<portrait=happy>If I don’t forget, that is. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to keep track of people’s birthdays, there’s a calendar near <NPCName>Sam</>’s General Store.//Don’t worry, I make sure to update it every season.//<portrait=happy>If I don’t forget, that is. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Giving birthday presents is the quickest way to make friends.//<portrait=happy>I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.
Text.LocalizedString: Giving birthday presents is the quickest way to make friends.//<portrait=happy>I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe it’s almost the weekend already?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe it’s almost the weekend already?

Text.SourceString: The week goes by really fast when you’re having fun – or have a lot to do.//<portrait=happy>Either way, a full week is always good week.
Text.LocalizedString: The week goes by really fast when you’re having fun – or have a lot to do.//<portrait=happy>Either way, a full week is always good week.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any plans for the weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any plans for the weekend?

Text.SourceString: I’ll probably go to the Tavern tonight and catch up with folks.//<portrait=happy>My favorite thing to do!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll probably go to the Tavern tonight and catch up with folks.//<portrait=happy>My favorite thing to do!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> makes a mean pasta.//The kids love it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> makes a mean pasta.//The kids love it.

Text.SourceString: Psst! <PlayerName>$Player</>, birthday presents are the quickest way to make friends.
Text.LocalizedString: Psst! <PlayerName>$Player</>, birthday presents are the quickest way to make friends.

Text.SourceString: I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.
Text.LocalizedString: I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.

Text.SourceString: Have you caught the new commercial on TV yet?//From what I’ve seen, <NpcName>Luke</> has an eye for quality electronics.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you caught the new commercial on TV yet?//From what I’ve seen, <NpcName>Luke</> has an eye for quality electronics.

Text.SourceString: Preparing for the new week, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Preparing for the new week, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: The weather is perfect for diving.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is perfect for diving.

Text.SourceString: I need to visit Socket & Pan today and ask <NpcName>Luke</> where my new blender is.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to visit Socket & Pan today and ask <NpcName>Luke</> where my new blender is.

Text.SourceString: Ah, darn… Socket is closed today.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, darn… Socket is closed today.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to treat myself to a pineapple upside-down cake today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to treat myself to a pineapple upside-down cake today.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sam</> carries a different variety of crops every year.//I hope he brings back durian next year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sam</> carries a different variety of crops every year.//I hope he brings back durian next year.

Text.SourceString: Durian sure is my guilty pleasure.
Text.LocalizedString: Durian sure is my guilty pleasure.

Text.SourceString: Even though I’m busy… I am, by the way! I have a lot on the agenda this season.//But even so, I still like to take fishing breaks here and there. Having the time to do things I like is important to me.//And the doctors agree!
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I’m busy… I am, by the way! I have a lot on the agenda this season.//But even so, I still like to take fishing breaks here and there. Having the time to do things I like is important to me.//And the doctors agree!

Text.SourceString: You should talk to <NpcName>Sunny</> at the Beach Shack if you have any questions about fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: You should talk to <NpcName>Sunny</> at the Beach Shack if you have any questions about fishing.

Text.SourceString: Yes, he’s <NpcName>Oliver’s</> dad, and he’s the one at the cash register.//<portrait=happy>Not the one in the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, he’s <NpcName>Oliver’s</> dad, and he’s the one at the cash register.//<portrait=happy>Not the one in the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: Some of the islanders like to do group yoga at the community center every Saturday morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the islanders like to do group yoga at the community center every Saturday morning.

Text.SourceString: <portrait=normal><NPCName>Leah</> usually leads the class.
Text.LocalizedString: <portrait=normal><NPCName>Leah</> usually leads the class.

Text.SourceString: Happy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Coral Island has very fertile soil.//You can grow almost anything here.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island has very fertile soil.//You can grow almost anything here.

Text.SourceString: And the fishing, of course.//You can catch salmon in the sea all Summer long.
Text.LocalizedString: And the fishing, of course.//You can catch salmon in the sea all Summer long.

Text.SourceString: We’re incredibly blessed here with the weather and the fertile soil, and not too much of a rat problem.//To give back, it’s important for us to take care of our environment.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re incredibly blessed here with the weather and the fertile soil, and not too much of a rat problem.//To give back, it’s important for us to take care of our environment.

Text.SourceString: The rats could be way worse.//<portrait=annoyed>I heard from a friend who’s also a mayor that rats destroyed their community center.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, it’s all restored now. It’s fine.
Text.LocalizedString: The rats could be way worse.//<portrait=annoyed>I heard from a friend who’s also a mayor that rats destroyed their community center.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, it’s all restored now. It’s fine.

Text.SourceString: Back in the day, I’d spend Saturdays at the beach from sunrise to sundown.//Ah, the good old days…
Text.LocalizedString: Back in the day, I’d spend Saturdays at the beach from sunrise to sundown.//Ah, the good old days…

Text.SourceString: Have you tried growing grass?//When you cut it, it’s automatically deposited into your silo as animal feed.//<portrait=happy>It might save you some money in the long run.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried growing grass?//When you cut it, it’s automatically deposited into your silo as animal feed.//<portrait=happy>It might save you some money in the long run.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NpcName>Ben</> has seeds that <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.//If you want to check it out, <NpcName>Ben</> is open today.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NpcName>Ben</> has seeds that <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.//If you want to check it out, <NpcName>Ben</> is open today.

Text.SourceString: I’m not exactly sure about <NpcName>Ben’s</> store hours.//<portrait=normal>I don’t go to that part of the forest very often. It’s too far for my knees.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not exactly sure about <NpcName>Ben’s</> store hours.//<portrait=normal>I don’t go to that part of the forest very often. It’s too far for my knees.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben’s</> usually out of town for the last two weeks of Fall.//He likes to go on adventures, that one.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben’s</> usually out of town for the last two weeks of Fall.//He likes to go on adventures, that one.

Text.SourceString: His eyes do always look red. He must not sleep very much.//<portrait=normal>That young man must have plenty of work to do.//I might go and check up on him next week.
Text.LocalizedString: His eyes do always look red. He must not sleep very much.//<portrait=normal>That young man must have plenty of work to do.//I might go and check up on him next week.

Text.SourceString: I think the last time I went to your farm was when you first moved to the island.//<portrait=happy>Do you remember that?
Text.LocalizedString: I think the last time I went to your farm was when you first moved to the island.//<portrait=happy>Do you remember that?

Text.SourceString: It feels like ages ago.//Now you’ve become part of the community.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like ages ago.//Now you’ve become part of the community.

Text.SourceString: Part of my job is to check in on local businesses and make sure they’re doing okay.//I also make sure their taxes are paid on time.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of my job is to check in on local businesses and make sure they’re doing okay.//I also make sure their taxes are paid on time.

Text.SourceString: I’ve spoken to the governor about lowering our taxes and increasing the school budget.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve spoken to the governor about lowering our taxes and increasing the school budget.

Text.SourceString: It isn’t in my power to change the law, but there’s nothing wrong with trying.
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t in my power to change the law, but there’s nothing wrong with trying.

Text.SourceString: Should we put in a request for an expanded library?//I could see it being beneficial to the islanders.
Text.LocalizedString: Should we put in a request for an expanded library?//I could see it being beneficial to the islanders.

Text.SourceString: But I’m not sure how I could get the funding.//It’s a bit tight with trying to keep our festivals running every year.//The governor may not like the idea much.
Text.LocalizedString: But I’m not sure how I could get the funding.//It’s a bit tight with trying to keep our festivals running every year.//The governor may not like the idea much.

Text.SourceString: Back in my youth, I used to run a general store downtown. But then Mayor Leanne passed away.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in my youth, I used to run a general store downtown. But then Mayor Leanne passed away.

Text.SourceString: At a town meeting, I decided to ask if I should run to replace her.//<portrait=happy>There seemed to be support for it, so I did.
Text.LocalizedString: At a town meeting, I decided to ask if I should run to replace her.//<portrait=happy>There seemed to be support for it, so I did.

Text.SourceString: I saw this town panic during a flu outbreak some years ago. People started stocking up on food, which depleted our food supply very fast.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw this town panic during a flu outbreak some years ago. People started stocking up on food, which depleted our food supply very fast.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, we got it contained quickly, and the hysteria settled.//But that was one expensive year for the town.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, we got it contained quickly, and the hysteria settled.//But that was one expensive year for the town.

Text.SourceString: I’m proud to say we have excellent doctors here.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m proud to say we have excellent doctors here.

Text.SourceString: I’m sure it’s just a matter of time before Coral Island attracts more talented people like you.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure it’s just a matter of time before Coral Island attracts more talented people like you.

Text.SourceString: I’ve spent my life taking care of Coral Island. I never got to take Carol to see the world, and now I spend sleepless nights regretting it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve spent my life taking care of Coral Island. I never got to take Carol to see the world, and now I spend sleepless nights regretting it.

Text.SourceString: I just don’t feel like traveling anymore. If it’s only me, is it even worth it?
Text.LocalizedString: I just don’t feel like traveling anymore. If it’s only me, is it even worth it?

Text.SourceString: A new week is right around the corner. Are you planting anything new at the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: A new week is right around the corner. Are you planting anything new at the farm?

Text.SourceString: I always have less work on the weekend, except for when we’re putting on a festival.
Text.LocalizedString: I always have less work on the weekend, except for when we’re putting on a festival.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see the youth getting more involved in the community.//The kids at the school volunteered to clean up the beach last week.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see the youth getting more involved in the community.//The kids at the school volunteered to clean up the beach last week.

Text.SourceString: You’re setting an excellent example for all of us, <PlayerName>$player</>. Keep up the good work!
Text.LocalizedString: You’re setting an excellent example for all of us, <PlayerName>$player</>. Keep up the good work!

Text.SourceString: How was your first week on the farm?//It’s been a while since anybody stayed in that cabin.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your first week on the farm?//It’s been a while since anybody stayed in that cabin.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too thrilled to announce Pufferfish’s arrival next week.//But the islanders need to know as soon as possible.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too thrilled to announce Pufferfish’s arrival next week.//But the islanders need to know as soon as possible.

Text.SourceString: They’re looking for land, you know.//<portrait=normal>The governor told me they were planning to purchase your farm, but it didn't go through. So they came here to look for another parcel to buy.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re looking for land, you know.//<portrait=normal>The governor told me they were planning to purchase your farm, but it didn't go through. So they came here to look for another parcel to buy.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish wants to start drilling on our island.//The only thing that stopped them from bringing their equipment here was that they didn’t have any property.//They want to buy us out, then drill as much oil as they can.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish wants to start drilling on our island.//The only thing that stopped them from bringing their equipment here was that they didn’t have any property.//They want to buy us out, then drill as much oil as they can.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish is building a mini golf course for the community. First they buy us off with gifts, then they’ll try to buy us out.//<portrait=concerned>I think as long as we don’t sell our land, we don’t have anything to worry about.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish is building a mini golf course for the community. First they buy us off with gifts, then they’ll try to buy us out.//<portrait=concerned>I think as long as we don’t sell our land, we don’t have anything to worry about.

Text.SourceString: Have you planted any Spring seeds yet?//<portrait=happy>Sugarcane is my personal favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you planted any Spring seeds yet?//<portrait=happy>Sugarcane is my personal favorite.

Text.SourceString: It does take a while to grow, but we grow the sweetest sugarcane here.//<portrait=happy>I’m sure <NpcName>Sam</> would pay a lot for it.
Text.LocalizedString: It does take a while to grow, but we grow the sweetest sugarcane here.//<portrait=happy>I’m sure <NpcName>Sam</> would pay a lot for it.

Text.SourceString: Spring is my least favorite season because…you know – taxes.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is my least favorite season because…you know – taxes.

Text.SourceString: Well, that was negative of me.//<portrait=happy>Spring is great, actually, with all the colorful tulips growing all over the island. Bamboo shoots!
Text.LocalizedString: Well, that was negative of me.//<portrait=happy>Spring is great, actually, with all the colorful tulips growing all over the island. Bamboo shoots!

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for Summer?//<portrait=happy>The beach is very lively this time of year!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for Summer?//<portrait=happy>The beach is very lively this time of year!

Text.SourceString: You should save some of your Spring vegetables in a chest in case you need them for something later.
Text.LocalizedString: You should save some of your Spring vegetables in a chest in case you need them for something later.

Text.SourceString: Letting the tax returns pile up can be mentally draining.//<portrait=normal>It’s good to get them done early.
Text.LocalizedString: Letting the tax returns pile up can be mentally draining.//<portrait=normal>It’s good to get them done early.

Text.SourceString: Remember, we have the Cherry Blossom Festival potluck tomorrow. There will be so much food!//See you there!
Text.LocalizedString: Remember, we have the Cherry Blossom Festival potluck tomorrow. There will be so much food!//See you there!

Text.SourceString: What better way to celebrate Spring, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to celebrate Spring, eh?

Text.SourceString: Summer is here! Ah, I can feel the sun on my skin! Life’s good, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: Summer is here! Ah, I can feel the sun on my skin! Life’s good, eh?

Text.SourceString: Are you going to plant pineapples this Summer? <NpcName>Sam</> might have seeds this year.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to plant pineapples this Summer? <NpcName>Sam</> might have seeds this year.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad <NpcName>Nina</> is coming to visit. I remember when she was born. The celebration was out of this world.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad <NpcName>Nina</> is coming to visit. I remember when she was born. The celebration was out of this world.

Text.SourceString: I usually spend my Summer weekends at the Beach Shack, catching up with <NpcName>Nina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually spend my Summer weekends at the Beach Shack, catching up with <NpcName>Nina</>.

Text.SourceString: I think I’m going to visit the <NpcName>Sanchezes</> tomorrow and see what they’ve been up to.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’m going to visit the <NpcName>Sanchezes</> tomorrow and see what they’ve been up to.

Text.SourceString: They’re a lot of fun to chat with. That <NpcName>Pablo</> always has some stories!
Text.LocalizedString: They’re a lot of fun to chat with. That <NpcName>Pablo</> always has some stories!

Text.SourceString: Now that the sun is blazing nonstop, I need this hat on me at all times.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that the sun is blazing nonstop, I need this hat on me at all times.

Text.SourceString: Summer is here!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer is here!

Text.SourceString: Are you having a productive Summer, <PlayerName>$player</>? Because I sure am.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you having a productive Summer, <PlayerName>$player</>? Because I sure am.

Text.SourceString: Plenty of people want to join our Harvest Festival. But with a limited budget, I have to make sure that local merchants get their booths first before opening them up to anybody else.
Text.LocalizedString: Plenty of people want to join our Harvest Festival. But with a limited budget, I have to make sure that local merchants get their booths first before opening them up to anybody else.

Text.SourceString: I hate policing the booths at festivals, but there are regulations that people need to follow. We can’t just approve every design. What if it looks out of place?
Text.LocalizedString: I hate policing the booths at festivals, but there are regulations that people need to follow. We can’t just approve every design. What if it looks out of place?

Text.SourceString: I wish someday somebody would create a warm fizzy drink with dried pumpkin in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish someday somebody would create a warm fizzy drink with dried pumpkin in it.

Text.SourceString: I’d call it “pumpkin extract drink.” Sounds good, doesn’t it?//<portrait=surprised>They have a pumpkin extract drink in Pokyo?! Lucky them!
Text.LocalizedString: I’d call it “pumpkin extract drink.” Sounds good, doesn’t it?//<portrait=surprised>They have a pumpkin extract drink in Pokyo?! Lucky them!

Text.SourceString: You probably can’t do all that much farming in this harsh weather, eh, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: You probably can’t do all that much farming in this harsh weather, eh, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: It might be a good time to check out different parts of the island. Or maybe make friends.
Text.LocalizedString: It might be a good time to check out different parts of the island. Or maybe make friends.

Text.SourceString: How’s the farm doing? I hope the old house is holding up okay.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the farm doing? I hope the old house is holding up okay.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t seen rain this hard since…hmm…//<portrait=happy>Since the last time it rained, I guess.//Apologies, rainy days make my head a bit fuzzy.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen rain this hard since…hmm…//<portrait=happy>Since the last time it rained, I guess.//Apologies, rainy days make my head a bit fuzzy.

Text.SourceString: I can’t hear you! Let’s go inside and continue our chat.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t hear you! Let’s go inside and continue our chat.

Text.SourceString: There’s something about rainy nights. So soothing.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something about rainy nights. So soothing.

Text.SourceString: No matter the season, it gets cold when it rains here.
Text.LocalizedString: No matter the season, it gets cold when it rains here.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]

Text.SourceString: Oh my! It’s been a while since we had a storm like this!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! It’s been a while since we had a storm like this!

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]

Text.SourceString: How are your plants holding up in the storm?
Text.LocalizedString: How are your plants holding up in the storm?

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Connor</> is hurrying somewhere.]

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?

Text.SourceString: Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.

Text.SourceString: Anyway, how’s your day been?
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, how’s your day been?

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?

Text.SourceString: Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.

Text.SourceString: Anyway, how’s your day been?
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, how’s your day been?

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t the way the town is covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?

Text.SourceString: Good day, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m happy to see the locals supporting each other.
Text.LocalizedString: Good day, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m happy to see the locals supporting each other.

Text.SourceString: I just had a good chat next door, and I thought I’d come by here to see what <NpcName>Luke</> has in stock.
Text.LocalizedString: I just had a good chat next door, and I thought I’d come by here to see what <NpcName>Luke</> has in stock.

Text.SourceString: How’s the farm doing?//I hope the old house is holding up okay.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the farm doing?//I hope the old house is holding up okay.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been sporting this hairstyle since I was eighteen.//Maybe it’s time for a change.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been sporting this hairstyle since I was eighteen.//Maybe it’s time for a change.

Text.SourceString: Nah! People seem to like it.//I’ll keep this style.
Text.LocalizedString: Nah! People seem to like it.//I’ll keep this style.

Text.SourceString: One of these days, I’ll show you my old general store.
Text.LocalizedString: One of these days, I’ll show you my old general store.

Text.SourceString: It’s right next door.//<NpcName>Luke</> runs an electronics store there now.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s right next door.//<NpcName>Luke</> runs an electronics store there now.

Text.SourceString: Hi, there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Enjoying yourself?
Text.LocalizedString: Hi, there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Enjoying yourself?

Text.SourceString: I’ve heard people say you shouldn’t mix business with pleasure.//Well, I don’t know what to tell ya, but I’m here to check up on local businesses.//<portrait=happy>It doesn’t mean I can’t enjoy myself, does it?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve heard people say you shouldn’t mix business with pleasure.//Well, I don’t know what to tell ya, but I’m here to check up on local businesses.//<portrait=happy>It doesn’t mean I can’t enjoy myself, does it?

Text.SourceString: I don’t think so.//<portrait=normal>To make a point, I’m about to show you how much fun I’m having.//Just hang on a minute. You don’t want to miss my classic dance moves.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think so.//<portrait=normal>To make a point, I’m about to show you how much fun I’m having.//Just hang on a minute. You don’t want to miss my classic dance moves.

Text.SourceString: I used to be quite the fun machine back in the day.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to be quite the fun machine back in the day.

Text.SourceString: What’s a Sunday without a little trip to the Tavern, right, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s a Sunday without a little trip to the Tavern, right, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’m debating whether I should take some cake home.//You know, for tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m debating whether I should take some cake home.//You know, for tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Don’t let me keep you from mingling!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t let me keep you from mingling!

Text.SourceString: Heh heh… I’ve heard that story at least three times now, and it gets funnier and funnier each time.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh… I’ve heard that story at least three times now, and it gets funnier and funnier each time.

Text.SourceString: The beach is stunning this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is stunning this time of year.

Text.SourceString: The sea right here, <PlayerName>$player</>, is home to many creatures.
Text.LocalizedString: The sea right here, <PlayerName>$player</>, is home to many creatures.

Text.SourceString: Fancy a room for a weekend getaway?
Text.LocalizedString: Fancy a room for a weekend getaway?

Text.SourceString: Just monitoring our tourism industry by collecting some data from <NpcName>Suki</>.//I’m also restocking the town’s brochures for the guests.
Text.LocalizedString: Just monitoring our tourism industry by collecting some data from <NpcName>Suki</>.//I’m also restocking the town’s brochures for the guests.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> helped me make the brochures.//Hmm… I see we could certainly use a new design.//<portrait=happy>This one is kind of outdated. Do you know anything about design, by any chance?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> helped me make the brochures.//Hmm… I see we could certainly use a new design.//<portrait=happy>This one is kind of outdated. Do you know anything about design, by any chance?

Text.SourceString: Do you know <NpcName>Joko</> and <NpcName>Dinda</> well?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know <NpcName>Joko</> and <NpcName>Dinda</> well?

Text.SourceString: Have you tried their pineapple upside-down cake?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried their pineapple upside-down cake?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give discounts.//<portrait=normal>I’ve known him for years and years, and I’ve never been given any sort of markdown.//Or even a rebate, for crying out loud.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give discounts.//<portrait=normal>I’ve known him for years and years, and I’ve never been given any sort of markdown.//Or even a rebate, for crying out loud.

Text.SourceString: Well, okay. <NpcName>Sam</> carries the best-quality produce, and to be fair, his prices aren’t too bad.//<portrait=happy>So, you’re right. I really can’t complain, can I?
Text.LocalizedString: Well, okay. <NpcName>Sam</> carries the best-quality produce, and to be fair, his prices aren’t too bad.//<portrait=happy>So, you’re right. I really can’t complain, can I?

Text.SourceString: Got all you need?
Text.LocalizedString: Got all you need?

Text.SourceString: Unbelievable view from up here.
Text.LocalizedString: Unbelievable view from up here.

Text.SourceString: My favorite part of town meetings is seeing us come together to tackle problem after problem. Doing that as a community feels special.//<portrait=concerned>Unfortunately, we don’t have a lot of them.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite part of town meetings is seeing us come together to tackle problem after problem. Doing that as a community feels special.//<portrait=concerned>Unfortunately, we don’t have a lot of them.

Text.SourceString: We don’t have enough problems to need more-frequent meetings.//<portrait=happy>I like the bonding. I guess that’s what festivals are for.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t have enough problems to need more-frequent meetings.//<portrait=happy>I like the bonding. I guess that’s what festivals are for.

Text.SourceString: I hope we have enough trash bins around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope we have enough trash bins around the island.

Text.SourceString: I’ve managed this town for too many years. Sometimes I wonder what my life would have been like if I’d never run for office.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve managed this town for too many years. Sometimes I wonder what my life would have been like if I’d never run for office.

Text.SourceString: Boring, perhaps!//But in retrospect, I could have traveled more.
Text.LocalizedString: Boring, perhaps!//But in retrospect, I could have traveled more.

Text.SourceString: Part of being the mayor of a small town is collecting local taxes.//<portrait=happy>It gives me a reason to get out of the house and visit folks.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of being the mayor of a small town is collecting local taxes.//<portrait=happy>It gives me a reason to get out of the house and visit folks.

Text.SourceString: I heard not all mayors do that. Every place has different rules, but I don’t mind collecting taxes.//<portrait=concerned>It’s not like I have a lot of things going on in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard not all mayors do that. Every place has different rules, but I don’t mind collecting taxes.//<portrait=concerned>It’s not like I have a lot of things going on in my life.

Text.SourceString: Wine is wine. Whether it’s good or bad, it tastes the same to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Wine is wine. Whether it’s good or bad, it tastes the same to me.

Text.SourceString: Remember to drink wine only in moderation.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to drink wine only in moderation.

Text.SourceString: Do you know what would make a great meal?//<portrait=happy>A pizza with pineapple!//I like the sweet taste.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know what would make a great meal?//<portrait=happy>A pizza with pineapple!//I like the sweet taste.

Text.SourceString: I was talking to <NpcName>Dippa</>, that talented painter who lives up behind my house. //<portrait=happy>They like it too! Pineapple on pizza.//<portrait=normal>I always liked them. Nice young couple, <NpcName>Dippa</> and <NpcName>Emma</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I was talking to <NpcName>Dippa</>, that talented painter who lives up behind my house. //<portrait=happy>They like it too! Pineapple on pizza.//<portrait=normal>I always liked them. Nice young couple, <NpcName>Dippa</> and <NpcName>Emma</>.

Text.SourceString: There are a few things that I regret in my life.//One of them is never taking my late wife to see the world.
Text.LocalizedString: There are a few things that I regret in my life.//One of them is never taking my late wife to see the world.

Text.SourceString: Maybe it’s not too late for me. After all, I always have her in my heart…
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe it’s not too late for me. After all, I always have her in my heart…

Text.SourceString: I must have slept wrong last night. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: I must have slept wrong last night. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: My right arm feels stiff. It hurt when I reached into the cupboard for tea this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: My right arm feels stiff. It hurt when I reached into the cupboard for tea this morning.

Text.SourceString: I count myself lucky to have so many friends here.//<portrait=concerned>It’s been very lonely since Carol passed away.
Text.LocalizedString: I count myself lucky to have so many friends here.//<portrait=concerned>It’s been very lonely since Carol passed away.

Text.SourceString: You gotta get yourself some friends like mine, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta get yourself some friends like mine, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: I hate to be the police of this town, but somebody has to uphold the town code.//<portrait=annoyed>I feel bad for telling <NpcName>Sam</> off about how to decorate his shop, but if I start letting him do whatever he wants, everybody else will want to do whatever they want.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to be the police of this town, but somebody has to uphold the town code.//<portrait=annoyed>I feel bad for telling <NpcName>Sam</> off about how to decorate his shop, but if I start letting him do whatever he wants, everybody else will want to do whatever they want.

Text.SourceString: Before you know it, it’s chaos.//Chaos, I tell you!
Text.LocalizedString: Before you know it, it’s chaos.//Chaos, I tell you!

Text.SourceString: If you could live forever, would you, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: If you could live forever, would you, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Ha ha! Not a bad take, I tell ya!
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha! Not a bad take, I tell ya!

Special.SourceString: Yes. Imagine all the things I’d get to try!
Special.LocalizedString: Yes. Imagine all the things I’d get to try!

Text.SourceString: I feel the same way.//I make sure to do something I like every day, no matter how small.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel the same way.//I make sure to do something I like every day, no matter how small.

Special.SourceString: No. I think there’s beauty in limits.
Special.LocalizedString: No. I think there’s beauty in limits.

Text.SourceString: Yes, I can understand that.//<portrait=normal>Although nobody can predict how long they’ll live. Not you, not me.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, I can understand that.//<portrait=normal>Although nobody can predict how long they’ll live. Not you, not me.

Special.SourceString: I don’t know. I have a long life ahead of me, and I don’t need to think about that.
Special.LocalizedString: I don’t know. I have a long life ahead of me, and I don’t need to think about that.

Text.SourceString: I’m starting to doubt my ability to run this island.//I’ve been feeling my age lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m starting to doubt my ability to run this island.//I’ve been feeling my age lately.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, it’s just the Winter blues.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, it’s just the Winter blues.

Text.SourceString: You’ve been a great help to this community.//<portrait=happy>I’m glad you chose to take over your family’s farm.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve been a great help to this community.//<portrait=happy>I’m glad you chose to take over your family’s farm.

Text.SourceString: We’re lucky to have you here.//Thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: We’re lucky to have you here.//Thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: I’m always torn between wanting to feel the fresh air in my hair and protecting my head from the sun. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m always torn between wanting to feel the fresh air in my hair and protecting my head from the sun. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Charles</> keeps telling me about sunscreen and hats. Oh <Italic>boy</>! It makes you think.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Charles</> keeps telling me about sunscreen and hats. Oh <Italic>boy</>! It makes you think.

Text.SourceString: Ever since I started living alone, there’s been a lot of bread in my diet.//So I decided to add more bok choy to my lunches lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever since I started living alone, there’s been a lot of bread in my diet.//So I decided to add more bok choy to my lunches lately.

Text.SourceString: Bok choy makes everything taste better.
Text.LocalizedString: Bok choy makes everything taste better.

Text.SourceString: Ever since I started living alone, there’s been a lot of bread in my diet.//So I decided to add more leafy vegetables to my lunches lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever since I started living alone, there’s been a lot of bread in my diet.//So I decided to add more leafy vegetables to my lunches lately.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to find bok choy in Spring, so I have to use lettuce.//<portrait=happy>It’s good, yeah, crunchy. But lettuce isn’t bok choy.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to find bok choy in Spring, so I have to use lettuce.//<portrait=happy>It’s good, yeah, crunchy. But lettuce isn’t bok choy.

Text.SourceString: We don’t hold town meetings often. We only have them to address specific important problems.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t hold town meetings often. We only have them to address specific important problems.

Text.SourceString: We already gather so often for festivals. It wouldn’t be efficient for me to clog up everyone’s calendars with meetings.//<portrait=happy>Though I wouldn’t be opposed. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: We already gather so often for festivals. It wouldn’t be efficient for me to clog up everyone’s calendars with meetings.//<portrait=happy>Though I wouldn’t be opposed. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I want to forget for a minute that I’m going home to an empty house at the end of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I want to forget for a minute that I’m going home to an empty house at the end of the day.

Text.SourceString: It’s harder to be positive on some days than others, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s harder to be positive on some days than others, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: I’m happy <NpcName>Luke</> can make good use of my old store space.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m happy <NpcName>Luke</> can make good use of my old store space.

Text.SourceString: It was much smaller back then. But then again, it was a much smaller community as well.
Text.LocalizedString: It was much smaller back then. But then again, it was a much smaller community as well.

Text.SourceString: Back in the day, the area behind my house was all forest. Trees everywhere!//The townies were far too scared to go there. You didn’t know what you might run into. Bears, wild boars, oh <Italic>boy</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Back in the day, the area behind my house was all forest. Trees everywhere!//The townies were far too scared to go there. You didn’t know what you might run into. Bears, wild boars, oh <Italic>boy</>!

Text.SourceString: Oh, this was way back when your grandparents were still here.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, this was way back when your grandparents were still here.

Text.SourceString: It makes me smile every time I see <NPCName>Taco</> or one of <NpcName>Erika’s</> cats.//I always make sure to stop and pet them, no matter how busy I am.
Text.LocalizedString: It makes me smile every time I see <NPCName>Taco</> or one of <NpcName>Erika’s</> cats.//I always make sure to stop and pet them, no matter how busy I am.

Text.SourceString: The little brown one with curly hair – ah, forgot the name.//Bonbon! Yes. That one is <Italic>barky</>, for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: The little brown one with curly hair – ah, forgot the name.//Bonbon! Yes. That one is <Italic>barky</>, for sure.

Text.SourceString: Do I ever miss running the store? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Do I ever miss running the store? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I guess not. I like being the mayor of this town.//I get to walk around and talk to people.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess not. I like being the mayor of this town.//I get to walk around and talk to people.

Text.SourceString: What kind of books do you like?
Text.LocalizedString: What kind of books do you like?

Text.SourceString: I’m shocked.//<portrait=annoyed>We have free books in the library. You should check them out sometime.//I mean, actually check them out to take home! Ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m shocked.//<portrait=annoyed>We have free books in the library. You should check them out sometime.//I mean, actually check them out to take home! Ha!

Text.SourceString: I have to say, it’s a popular genre.//Fantasy is my weakness too. I can lose hours!
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say, it’s a popular genre.//Fantasy is my weakness too. I can lose hours!

Text.SourceString: I’m that way too. Great minds! Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>Bestsellers are usually what I’m drawn to.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m that way too. Great minds! Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>Bestsellers are usually what I’m drawn to.

Special.SourceString: Any good ones, really. Nothing specific.
Special.LocalizedString: Any good ones, really. Nothing specific.

Text.SourceString: *murmuring to himself* Do I really need a new blender?//Yes, I do.
Text.LocalizedString: *murmuring to himself* Do I really need a new blender?//Yes, I do.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to pick up some donations from Socket.//<NpcName>Luke</> is a very charitable young man.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to pick up some donations from Socket.//<NpcName>Luke</> is a very charitable young man.

Text.SourceString: His parents are major donors to this town.//They remind me of <NpcName>Nina’s</>. If I’m not mistaken, her parents were good friends with the Duckorns.
Text.LocalizedString: His parents are major donors to this town.//They remind me of <NpcName>Nina’s</>. If I’m not mistaken, her parents were good friends with the Duckorns.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke’s</> parents are major donors to this town.//They remind me of <NpcName>Nina’s</>. If I’m not mistaken, her parents were good friends with the Duckornses.//Their families spent a lot of time together. Picnics at the beach, birthday parties… Things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke’s</> parents are major donors to this town.//They remind me of <NpcName>Nina’s</>. If I’m not mistaken, her parents were good friends with the Duckornses.//Their families spent a lot of time together. Picnics at the beach, birthday parties… Things like that.

Text.SourceString: Even so, I rarely saw <NpcName>Nina’s</> dad out.//It was usually the mom, one of the nannies, and <NpcName>Nina</>. Never the dad.//<portrait=normal>Great man, though. Charitable heart. He was very giving.
Text.LocalizedString: Even so, I rarely saw <NpcName>Nina’s</> dad out.//It was usually the mom, one of the nannies, and <NpcName>Nina</>. Never the dad.//<portrait=normal>Great man, though. Charitable heart. He was very giving.

Text.SourceString: I buy extra kitchen appliances when I have the money.//I don’t use them all myself. No, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Don’t be silly.
Text.LocalizedString: I buy extra kitchen appliances when I have the money.//I don’t use them all myself. No, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=happy>Don’t be silly.

Text.SourceString: I ship them to a women’s shelter in the city. Donate them in Carol’s name.//She used to do that. I’m only carrying on her legacy.
Text.LocalizedString: I ship them to a women’s shelter in the city. Donate them in Carol’s name.//She used to do that. I’m only carrying on her legacy.

Text.SourceString: If you’re thinking of buying an appliance, you should get it now.//Because it may not be there tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re thinking of buying an appliance, you should get it now.//Because it may not be there tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: As <NpcName>Luke’s</> biggest customer, I probably shouldn’t be giving out shopping tips.//<portrait=happy>I’ve bought too many things there.
Text.LocalizedString: As <NpcName>Luke’s</> biggest customer, I probably shouldn’t be giving out shopping tips.//<portrait=happy>I’ve bought too many things there.

Text.SourceString: It’s Spring, but <Italic>boy</>! Do you feel the wind?//It goes straight through my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Spring, but <Italic>boy</>! Do you feel the wind?//It goes straight through my bones.

Text.SourceString: The Winter wind is still here. Brrrr.
Text.LocalizedString: The Winter wind is still here. Brrrr.

Text.SourceString: I got some hot peppers from <NPCName>Sam</>’s the other day and put them in my soup.//<portrait=surprised>Whoa! Too spicy. It wasn’t for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I got some hot peppers from <NPCName>Sam</>’s the other day and put them in my soup.//<portrait=surprised>Whoa! Too spicy. It wasn’t for me.

Text.SourceString: I like red curry, but this one was different. Maybe I added too many hot peppers.//<portrait=happy>It wasn’t kind to my stomach.
Text.LocalizedString: I like red curry, but this one was different. Maybe I added too many hot peppers.//<portrait=happy>It wasn’t kind to my stomach.

Text.SourceString: Do you notice anything different about my hat?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you notice anything different about my hat?

Text.SourceString: It’s a cactus! I thought I’d change things up a little. Keep it summery.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a cactus! I thought I’d change things up a little. Keep it summery.

Text.SourceString: I found a fairy rose the other day, and I thought I’d change things up a little with my hat.//<portrait=normal>Am I appropriate for Fall now?
Text.LocalizedString: I found a fairy rose the other day, and I thought I’d change things up a little with my hat.//<portrait=normal>Am I appropriate for Fall now?

Text.SourceString: It’s too cold to wear my other hats. I need one with ear flaps.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too cold to wear my other hats. I need one with ear flaps.

Text.SourceString: I couldn’t find any flowers for my hat, so I’m going through Winter <Italic>accessory-less</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn’t find any flowers for my hat, so I’m going through Winter <Italic>accessory-less</>.

Text.SourceString: My hat is missing its personality now. Hmm… Pins might not be a bad idea.//<portrait=normal>I always see <NpcName>Eleanor</> wearing butterfly pins. I should ask her where she got them.
Text.LocalizedString: My hat is missing its personality now. Hmm… Pins might not be a bad idea.//<portrait=normal>I always see <NpcName>Eleanor</> wearing butterfly pins. I should ask her where she got them.
